Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I control click and select both of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I can go into my Level->Group,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're gonna group these objects, we call this dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.76,0:03:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we did this is because now we can select both of them together
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.77,0:03:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll scale as they should.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.96,0:03:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a nice little way of how to set up everything
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.34,0:03:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to work for you and not against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have the dock right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.58,0:03:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe it's not exactly set up for a little path.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.42,0:03:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we can do is go back to our create object,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.08,0:03:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we can go to miscellaneous, let's choose road,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but before I do that, I want to make sure that I have terrain snapping on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.62,0:03:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can turn off the grid snapping as well, this won't matter as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.06,0:03:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm gonna click the road
