Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we need to do now is we need to actually select the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we click in the override material,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.98,0:04:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we're gonna wait for it to boot up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.36,0:04:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we go to the materials/roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.84,0:04:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and let's go ahead and do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.76,0:04:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,probably a road... a road_gravel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have a gravel road which...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,here's something that is very interesting regarding roads is you can align them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.00,0:04:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so if I take off my align to terrain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I push this down just a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.80,0:04:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and align the height map,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:05:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have a custom height map that drops with it from the actual door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.78,0:05:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we've created the house, we've created the path,
